cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.GT, cs.RO 

This paper is about a hybrid approach to reinforcement learning that combines model-based and model-free methods. It specifically focuses on using generative adversarial networks (GANs) to simulate rollouts in Monte-Carlo Tree Search (MCTS). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, since the GANs are used for image-to-image transduction, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the planning aspect of MCTS, which falls under cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.RO (Robotics).
